description: The only cartoon strip to focus on life after kids, pets, and a career, The Elderberries is Hogan's Heroes set in a retirement community. As more than a third of our nation's population strolls into senior citizenry, cartoonists Phil Frank and Joe Troise present The Elderberries--a heartwarming strip that follows the lives of five aging friends who reside at Elderpark, the "good place to park your elder." The residents of Elderpark include Dusty, the General, the Professor, Boone, and Evelyn, along with Miss Overdunne, who manages the property for the corporate bean counters at Jujitsu Heavy Industries (based in Hong Kong). Covert field trips, practical jokes, and dueling games of poker and word play keep this spirited group of elders one step ahead of ailments and the anarchy of aging. This is the first Elderberries book collection.

description: Think the world's nothing but a sinkhole of violence, racism, sexism, and homophobia? Afraid your old man has better weed than you? Terry Laban's Eno and Plum is just the thing to float your boat! It's a mutant cross between the Freak Brothers and Archie Comics! This trade paperback collects stories from CUD Comics, DHP, and Fantagraphics, plus an all-new, five-page strip.
name: TPB

description:
A powerless Dynagirl seeks the help of a voodoo priestess as she struggles to find a path through a seemingly insurmountable enemy and back home to her friends and family.

A single mother superhero who recently un-retired from fighting crime now juggles motherhood and hero work as she deals with the ghosts of a past that refuses to let her go.

After escaping from Glitch, Dynagirl and Amelia venture into the depths of a volcano to seek the help of a priestess to somehow gain enough power to defeat an enemy that steals powers!
name: Heart of Fire

description: Cavewoman: Oasis is a new 2 issue mini-series by Devon Massey featuring his beautifully done ink-washed artwork. Beautiful girls are missing in Marshville and it's up to Meriem to find out why. Tracking her quarry across the burning sands of the Pangaean desert, Meriem discovers an oasis and a secret desert city ruled by a sinister Master, intent on adding Meriem to his collection of beautiful captives. Meriem infiltrates the harem but is soon discovered and now must survive as a gladiator in the Master's arena, the Bowl of Bones, where she battles the greatest warriors in the Pangaean desert and the deadliest dinosaurs of the burning sands.
name: Mystery Moon

description: For decades World War 2 super-soldier Captain America lay in frozen suspended-animation, encased in ice, until he was revived in the modern world to again take his post of protector of the Red, White and Blue. But when a mysterious package arrives at his door and he crosses paths with a shadowy new villain named The Interrogator, Captain America learns that everything about this past, his memories, and himself, may not be what it seems! COLLECTING CAPTAIN AMERICA #12-16.
name: Volume 3
